summary: some people in the fandom: you all hate sansa because she is very feminine and doesn’t go around having sex or being more manly,...
body:
some people in the fandom: you all hate sansa because she is very feminine and doesn’t go around having sex or being more manly, that’s misogyny and sexism!

same people in the fandom: brienne and arya don’t perform femininity despite being females because there is only ONE type of femininity, if you don’t follow that, you’re not being a female

defeinition of sexism: noun, “treatment of men and women based on the belief that particular jobs and activities are suitable only for men and others are suitable only for women”

same people in the fandom: arya is also very misogynist and sexist! 

arya: “women are important too!” // “i’m a girl.”

me:  ¯\_(ツ)_/¯

title: Anything for You
body:
Elisabeth’s eyes widened considerably and her cheeks flushed. It was a welcome sight to Jon - he’d grown tired of blood and guts and all the ugly things he’d seen in his short life. He longed to see more things as beautiful as she was in that moment.

.

The long winter had finally come, and people were dropping like flies. It was bitterly cold and food was running low. Everyone had lost someone during the great battles that had taken place, some more…

Read more…
